[1] Philippines, Mindanao
Date: Tue 15 Mar 2016
Source: Mindanao Times [edited]
http://mindanaotimes.net/15500-has-of-banana-farms-affected-by-disease-official/


15 500 ha of banana farms affected by disease
----------------------------------------------
Panama disease has already affected 15 500 hectares of banana farms in the Davao Region, especially those owned by small growers, according to 2015 data from the Department of Agriculture (DA).

Virgelio Gutierrez, DA [region] XI, said that they are providing interventions to the growers. Davao del Norte [is] the province that was largely hit by the disease, followed by Compostela Valley. "We have so far assisted 710 banana farmers," he said.

He said they have so far provided 45 000 Giant Cavendish Tissue-Cultured Variant 219, which was proven to be resistant of the disease. This variety is only given to those whose farms have 5 percent and above Fusarium Wilt infection.

Those banana farms with 5 percent and below infection were advised to do proper eradication protocols. DA XI also provided trichoderma harzianum, a beneficial fungus that could help manage the spread of the disease.

The Pilipino Banana Growers and Exporters Association has requested the DA to come up with a mapping of the affected areas by the disease.

[Byline: Kristianne Fusilero]

